duplicatelist



class DuplicateList;
Keeps track of a list of duplicate entries to be written to a readable text file.

void add(string typeName, WAD wadA, string nameA, const int indexA, WAD wadB, string nameB, const int indexB, immutable bool merged);
Adds a new duplicate entry.

Params:
string typeName The type of entry.
WAD wadA The WAD that the first entry is in.
string nameA The name of the first entry.
int indexA The index of the first entry.
WAD wadB The WAD that the second entry is in.
string nameB The WAD that the second entry.
int indexB The index of the second entry.
bool merged If true, this duplicate was resolved by merging isntead of overwriting.

void add(DuplicateList other);
Adds another duplicate list's entries to this one.

Params:
DuplicateList other The DuplicateList to add entries from.

protected Duplicate[] getDuplicates();
Returns:
An array of Duplicate entries.

void writeTo(string fileName);
Writes all duplicate entries to a readable text file.

Params:
string fileName The file to write to.
